
- RQ004 describe TMPLDIR definition
- RQ003 describe replacement rules
- RQ002 add GPL License information
- RQ001 make template list configurable

RQ001 make template list configurable
=====================================

The generation of the target files from the templates is controlled by
the transformation table. This transformation table contains the information:

For each template_name a list of template file names and their target name.

 template file name => target file expression
 cpp.cpp            => @Target@.cpp
 cpp.h              => @Target.h

The template file name allows relative paths based on the template directory (TMPLDIR).

The target file name generation is evaluated using the replacement rules (RPLRULES).

RQ004 describe TMPLDIR definition
================================

The template directory is determined in the following order. On every step, mksource
checks whether the referenced directory exists. If yes, mksource uses this directory
as TMPLDIR. If not, the next step is executed:

1. Check if a TMPLDIR environment variable is set. If yes, use the string as TMPLDIR.
2. Check if a TMPLDIR configuration variable is set. If yes, use the string as TMPLDIR.
3. Use the directory ~/etc/mksource_templates.
4. Use the directory /user/local/etc/mksource_directories
5. Use the directory /etc/mksource_templates


